profile_positions.description:
As a Principle Consultant of Global FinQuality - a consulting company, I offered a range of consulting services to banks and microfinance institutions (MFIs) in emerging markets around the globe mainly in risk management. 

Among my projects, commissioned by Appui au Developpement Autonome A.s.b.l. (ADA), I conducted risk management assessments of 3 financial institutions in Central Asia using the Risk Management Graduation Model (RMGM) developed by PRMIA based on global best practices in risk management. Microfinance institutions (MFIs) involved were: two affiliated MFIs – OXUS Tajikistan and OXUS Kyrgyzstan of OXUS Holding - a leading French NGO and Balyk Finance - the 3rd biggest MFI in Kyrgyzstan.

•	Reviewed the MFIs’ risk management systems (policies, procedures, business processes, limits, tools), verified daily practices (on-site visits of branches) and conducted interviews with the relevant staff including Board of Directors (BoD) and management to identify gaps in their risk management system; 
•	Identified the MFIs’ adherence to the best practices by summarizing how the MFIs scored on strategic, governance, credit, financial, operational risks;
•	Wrote comprehensive reports summarizing the assessment findings and giving detailed recommendations on how to improve the risk management system of the MFIs within 5 year;
•	Conducted workshops to discuss the assessment results the MFIs’ management and supported them in developing strategic one-year action plan to strengthen institutional capacities for risk management; 
•	Conducted workshops for the MFIs’ BoD to present the assessment results and action plan;
•	Trained the MFIs’ risk managers on Risk Management Graduation Model so that they could reassess the risk management system and produce one year action plan every year with a five-year horizon.

Oikocredit Int. is a Global Social Impact Investment Fund. I was responsible for building-up, managing and monitoring an investment portfolio of € 30 mln. consisting of 12 banks and MFIs in the Caucasus (Georgia, Armenia, Azerbaijan).

•	Developed a business strategy and a sales pipeline for the Caucasus region;
•	Built-up investment portfolio through identification of feasible loan & investment opportunities;
•	Conducted sector analysis and due diligence of banks and MFIs;
•	Defined project viability risk (environmental, social & governance (ESC) and risk scorecards);
•	Negotiated and prepared investment proposals;
•	Conducted customer due diligence (CDD) of clients acoording to the internal AML/AFT policy; 
•	Built up and maintained good relationships with partners and other stakeholders;
•	Developed new market opportunities: products and markets;
•	Represented Oikocredit Int. in the region at relevant network events; 
•	Identified a strategy for defaulted loans and participated in loan workout groups;
•	Implemented capacity building and social performance management (SPM) programs.

Bolder Group (former Circle Partners) - a Global Investment Fund Administrator. I supported the Board of Directors and management of Circle Partners in identifying, developing and implementing potential growth opportunities.

•	Participated in the strategic business planning process;
•	Collaborated with colleagues on the private equity business plan development;
•	Led the development of a new product – investor transparency and risk management tool;
•	Worked on the corporate brand and product marketing development;
•	Developed a quarterly marketing report;
•	Designed and implemented marketing campaigns, materials and advertisements;
•	Organized and participated in industry events (conferences, workshops, etc.).
